We started with dataset selection:
Mobifall was used for training of models as mobifall have data of sensors in different records. So data was segemented according to sensors one segment for accelrometer and one for gyroscopes.
Two LSTM models were trained one of accelerometer and one omn gyroscope data both of the models will give certain probabilty of that record 
one threshold is taken like acc_prob*0.3+gyro_prob > 0.5 then it is considered as fall scenarios the window is of size 50.


In Wearbles model TCN autoencoder is used to detect anomalies in wearbes data. Data was collected form fitbit dataset available on kaggle
hourly_calories, hourly_heartrate. hourly_steps, and hourly_intensity was considered for model training 

accuracy of each model is there in its ipynb file
